flowRoot.flowPara: Help & Support

Possibly the easiest way to get help with Xubuntu is to join our support Internet Relay Chat (IRC) channel, #xubuntu on the Freenode IRC network. To do this, navigate to xubuntu.org/irc to join the channel via a web interface or use your favorite IRC client.
Official documentation is shipped with each release of Xubuntu. Find it by navigating the main menu and selecting Help. In addition, the documentation is available online at docs.xubuntu.org.

Furthermore, we have many more support methods available, including a mailing list and a Frequently Asked Questions section on our website. For the complete list of support methods, navigate to xubuntu.org/help.
Contribute to Xubuntu

Xubuntu is always looking for new developers, artists, technical writers, reviewers and more to join the community! Learn more about the what you can do and how you can do it at xubuntu.org/contribute.
By the community, for the community Xubuntu is a completely volunteer-driven project that depends upon talents from people such as yourself to contribute. No one is paid to work directly on Xubuntu.
Local communities

If you want to learn more about Xubuntu, but would rather do it in your own language, don't worry! There are many local communities around the world who organize all kind of events to spread the word and help other people. You can even contribute back to Ubuntu via your local community.
To find your local community, go to loco.ubuntu.com.
